The paper deals with the optimization of convolutional neural networks using an evolutionary algorithm, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The focus of the paper is on image classification, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of evolutionary algorithms for optimization is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which can be seen as a form of optimization in game theory (cs.GT).
